<div class="section">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p>In my many efforts to find a subaltern artifact that I could find some personal connection to, I came across a New York Times article about something called Art Adds. In January 2010, three NYC artists had their work featured on taxi cab cones in this project organized by Show Media and the Art Production fund. Shirin Neshat was one of these artists, and her mixed media piece <em>Offered Eyes</em> (1993) was the work chosen to be displayed. I didn’t know a lot about the artist then, but I did know that like myself, she was of Persian descent, and that she was critically acclaimed by Iranians and Americans alike.<sup>1</sup></p>
